In Task 2, I created and updated my profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle. These platforms are important for students because they help in 
building a professional digital presence and showcasing skills and learning progress.GitHub is used for storing and sharing projects, especially 
coding-related work, and helps in building a technical portfolio. LinkedIn is a professional networking platform where students can present their
education, skills, and career interests, and connect with professionals. Kaggle is mainly used for learning data science, exploring datasets, and 
practicing real-world problems.Over the next four years, I plan to use GitHub to upload my projects and improve my coding skills. I will use 
LinkedIn to build connections, explore internship opportunities, and develop a professional identity. I will use Kaggle to learn more about data 
science and improve my analytical skills. These platforms will help me in academic growth as well as future career opportunities.
